我来总结一下"改变"这一课:A B C三点因素

502
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:18,230
The three are interconnected.
三点是相互关联

503
00:29:18,470 --> 00:29:21,000
In fact,if we want real change to come about,
事实上 如果我们真的想有所改变

504
00:29:21,250 --> 00:29:23,040
they have to be interconnected.
必须将这三点紧密连接起来

505
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:26,390
Why? Because habit is like a flood.
为什么?因为习惯就像洪水一样

506
00:29:26,800 --> 00:29:29,830
And it's not enough if we just create a small nook
如果我们只是开一个凹角或一条小缝

507
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:33,440
or cranny trying to create a new habit.
是不足以养成一个新习惯

508
00:29:33,630 --> 00:29:35,100
Because flood would wash it away.
因为洪水会将它冲走

509
00:29:35,430 --> 00:29:38,190
What we need is the A,the B and the C.
我们需要的是结合A B和C

510
00:29:38,930 --> 00:29:41,120
Implement these changes in our lives.
将这些变化融入我们生活中

511
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:45,290
And they are interconnected.So let me give you an example.
它们是内部相连的 举一个例子

512
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:47,870
Let's say someone who has low self-esteem.
例如那些自尊心很弱的人

513
00:29:48,300 --> 00:29:51,800
Low self-esteem,the C- cognition:
低自尊心 C 认知

514
00:29:52,020 --> 00:29:54,760
they don't think highly of themselves.
他们会小瞧自己

515
00:29:55,190 --> 00:29:56,880
Poor self evaluation.
自我评价低

516
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:59,310
When you don't think highly of yourself,
当你瞧不起自己时

517
00:29:59,570 --> 00:30:03,070
you are more likely to be innervated,to feel down,
就会比较内向 感觉没自信

518
00:30:03,970 --> 00:30:07,840
not to be motivated,and as a result of that,that is the Affect,
更别说有动力了 也因此而产生不良影响

519
00:30:08,070 --> 00:30:10,630
the emotion that you experience- not good feelings;
产生不好的情感

520
00:30:11,010 --> 00:30:13,970
as a result of that,we are much more likely to do nothing-
因此很可能会变得碌碌无为

521
00:30:14,740 --> 00:30:17,310
in other words,the B is do nothing.
也就是说 B是碌碌无为

522
00:30:17,580 --> 00:30:19,670
Now through self-perception theory,
通过自我认知理论

523
00:30:19,930 --> 00:30:23,170
the behavior then affects my cognition on doing nothing:
这种行为进而影响我对碌碌无为的认知

524
00:30:23,390 --> 00:30:26,260
I'm not dealing.I'm not coping.I'm avoiding.
我处理不了事情 我逃避事情

525
00:30:27,580 --> 00:30:30,190
And that lowers my self esteem,
这会使自尊降低

526
00:30:30,410 --> 00:30:34,160
even more my evaluation of myself,the C.
进而使自我评价更低 就是C

527
00:30:34,490 --> 00:30:37,300
And that leads to even worse emotions
这导致更低落的情感

528
00:30:37,590 --> 00:30:40,310
and so on and so on and so on,in a downward spiral,
等等 形成一个向下的螺旋

529
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:43,880
until in some cases,we reach resignation,
直到在某些情况下 我们自我放弃了

530
00:30:44,130 --> 00:30:47,040
or in Martin Seligman's words,learned helplessness.
或用Martin Seligman的话来说 就是"习得性无助"

531
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:50,610
Now think of someone who has high self-esteem,
现在 想想那些自尊心强的人

532
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:52,360
high level of self-confidence.
他们很有自信

533
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,260
I believe in myself.I think I can do well.
我相信自己 我认为我能做好

534
00:30:55,490 --> 00:30:58,170
That leads to high level of motivation.
那样会导致高水平的激励

535
00:30:58,770 --> 00:31:00,600
Remember what Marva Collins does?
记得Marva Collins是怎么做的吗?

536
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:02,570
The model that we talked about under belief,
我们讲过的关于信仰的模型

537
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:04,450
self-fulfilling prophecies-
自我实现预言

538
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:07,960
that leads to high levels of motivations,strong emotions.
能提高个人动机和导致强烈的情感

539
00:31:08,220 --> 00:31:10,010
I'm energized.
我充满动力

540
00:31:10,590 --> 00:31:15,730
And that in turn leads to more action- the B,the behaviors.
也反过来引发更多的行动 就是B 行为

541
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:18,870
Because I act more,I do more,I cope more.
因为我做得更多 我应对的就更多

542
00:31:19,100 --> 00:31:20,840
I put myself on the line more.
我更多地把自己置于水平线上

543
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:25,930
I'm much more likely to have more positive evaluation of myself,
那我对自己的积极评价就会更高些

544
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:29,070
which leads to more positive emotions and on and on and on,
因此也会产生更多积极情绪等等

545
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:30,840
in an upward spiral.
呈现一个上升的螺旋

546
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:33,650
The spiral that Barbara Fredrickson talks about
也就是Barbara Fredrickson所说的螺旋

547
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:38,590
in the Broaden-and-build,the spiral that Bandura talks about
他在"拓延-建构"中谈到

548
00:31:38,850 --> 00:31:40,820
when he discusses self-efficacy.
自我能效时所提到的螺旋

549
00:31:43,740 --> 00:31:46,640
When we intervene,it's important to introduce,
既然涉及到这方面 就很有必要介绍一下了

550
00:31:47,540 --> 00:31:49,360
if possible,all three.
可以的话 三点我都想说说

551
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:51,420
And we can start anywhere.
从哪里说起都可以

552
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:54,690
So let's take an example- someone with socialphobia,
我举个例子 例如一个有社交恐惧症的人

553
00:31:54,930 --> 00:31:57,910
someone who is afraid to be out there,in front of people.
一个害怕社交活动 不善与人交际的人

554
00:31:59,330 --> 00:32:00,430
One way to deal with it-
治疗这种症状的一种方法…

555
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:03,140
let's begin with the A,the Affect,the emotion.
我们先从A说起 就是影响 也就是情感

556
00:32:03,590 --> 00:32:07,570
One way to deal with it is through medication
其中一方面是药物治疗

557
00:32:07,820 --> 00:32:10,300
that goes directly to our emotions.
直接影响我们的情绪

558
00:32:11,550 --> 00:32:14,220
Another way of dealing with it is meditation,
另一方面是冥想

559
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:17,140
which also affects our emotions directly.
同样直接影响我们的情绪

560
00:32:18,170 --> 00:32:20,940
Some people benefit more from one,or from the other-
有些人比较适合第一种 有的适合第二种

561
00:32:21,420 --> 00:32:24,220
depends on how extreme the situation is.
这取决于他的状况有多极端

562
00:32:24,490 --> 00:32:26,300
But that's the A,the Affect.
这是A 影响

563
00:32:26,530 --> 00:32:29,030
One way of dealing with it,behavior,
另一种治疗方法 行为

564
00:32:29,270 --> 00:32:33,310
is through what's called in cognitive behavioral therapy,exposure
通过所谓的认知行为疗法来进行 曝光

565
00:32:33,530 --> 00:32:39,180
which is gradual exposure to stimuli that create that phobia.
逐步将自己曝光在产生这种恐惧的刺激物前

566
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:43,370
So initially I'll walk,you know,10 yards out of my home.
首先 先走出家门10码

567
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:46,840
Initially exposure through the imagination
先通过想象来曝光

568
00:32:47,060 --> 00:32:48,400
and I include it under behavior,
之后付诸实践

569
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:49,870
because the mind does know the difference
因为我们的大脑分不清楚…

570
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:52,440
between the imaginary and the real.
想象和现实的差异

571
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,880
So gradually being exposed to it.
逐渐走出更远

572
00:32:56,060 --> 00:32:58,380
Over time being exposed more and more,
随着时间推移 曝光度越来越高

573
00:32:58,590 --> 00:33:02,000
until I can go out to a mall
直到我可以去到一个商场

574
00:33:02,330 --> 00:33:06,200
and not experience the same anxiety that I did a year ago.
并再也没有一年前那种焦虑

575
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:08,030
So that's through behavior.
这就是行为治疗法

576
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:10,760
Very effective- the exposure technique.
很有效 曝光的方法

577
00:33:11,190 --> 00:33:16,730
And finally,you can also intervene through cognition in therapy,
最后 在治疗过程中还能介入认知

578
00:33:17,050 --> 00:33:21,060
in dealing with irrational thoughts,psychological traps,
来处理不理智的想法 心理困惑

579
00:33:21,250 --> 00:33:24,190
the three M's- "Am I magnifying? The extent.
那三个M "我有将事情放大吗

580
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:26,120
Am I minimizing something?
我有轻视了自己的一些才能吗?

581
00:33:26,370 --> 00:33:29,720
For example,my successes in working with people.
例如小瞧了自己在与人相处方面的成功

582
00:33:29,980 --> 00:33:33,930
Or am I making up? Imaginary scenarios.
我有在编造事实 想象情景吗?

583
00:33:34,230 --> 00:33:38,870
My catastrophizing events when I can have a more realistic view."
本可以更现实地看待的事情 我有将它灾难化吗?

584
00:33:39,130 --> 00:33:41,620
So that's my thinking about it,the cognition.
这就是我的想法 认知

585
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:45,810
Let me show you a personal example of something that I dealt with
跟你们说说我克服某种困难的做法

586
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:52,690
So as you know,born through genes- high levels of anxiety.
你们知道 我天生就很容易焦虑

587
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:53,740
Very prone to it.
我很容易焦虑

588
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:56,740
Startle very easily- still,less today,
容易吃惊 容易被惊吓 现在好一点了

589
00:33:56,970 --> 00:33:58,950
but still to some extent today.
但还是会容易吃惊

590
00:33:59,230 --> 00:34:00,910
Used to get very nervous in squash matches.
以前参加壁球比赛时非常紧张

591
00:34:01,100 --> 00:34:06,250
Used to choke often,when I was playing important games.
在重要比赛时常常呼吸困难

592
00:34:07,250 --> 00:34:08,850
And that's something that in front of,
但我面对的事实是

593
00:34:09,070 --> 00:34:12,170
speaking in front of an audience,got very nervous and anxious.
要在观众面前讲话 非常紧张和焦虑

594
00:34:12,430 --> 00:34:13,340
And this is something that I decided
我决定要…

595
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:15,370
that I really wanted to deal with.
克服这种心理

596
00:34:15,640 --> 00:34:18,550
More than any other things that I was facing.The thing anxiety.
我面临的最大困难不是其他 而是焦虑

597
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:24,070
So what did I do? Let me begin first with the C,Cognition.
那我是怎么做的呢 我先从C 认知说起

598
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:28,290
What I did- I analyzed the situation in my journal.
我分析了我日记中的情况

599
00:34:28,770 --> 00:34:32,040
I used the Bureau of Study Counsel.
利用学校咨询机构

600
00:34:32,710 --> 00:34:36,320
I learned and studied about the three M's,
学习并研究了关于三个M的知识

601
00:34:38,510 --> 00:34:38,970
the irrational thoughts-
那三种不理智的想法

602
00:34:39,270 --> 00:34:43,390
magnifying,minimizing,making up,catastrophizing.
将事情扩大化 缩小化 编造情景 灾难化

603
00:34:44,470 --> 00:34:46,330
And through cognition,it helped a lot.
通过认知 我得到了很大的帮助

604
00:34:46,570 --> 00:34:48,320
That wasn't enough.
但那远远不够

605
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:52,320
After the C,I went to the A,the Affect.
学习了C之后 我开始学习A 影响

606
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:57,320
And the Affect was for me physical exercise.
影响是通过身体锻炼来实现的

607
00:34:57,670 --> 00:35:00,730
You know,even today,this morning,at home,I ran.
直到今天 早上我还跑过步

608
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,530
I exercise because
我锻炼身体是因为…

609
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:06,680
it significantly lowers anyone's levels of anxiety.
它能大大降低我们的焦虑水平

610
00:35:06,910 --> 00:35:10,250
And I can tell a significant difference in my talks
可以说如果我不锻炼身体 我的口才…

611
00:35:10,580 --> 00:35:11,740
if I don't exercise.
一定不会像现在这么好

612
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:17,770
So even three or four weeks ago,David,my son was unwell
甚至在三四周前 我儿子David身体不适

613
00:35:17,990 --> 00:35:20,510
and I had to take him to the doctor first thing Tuesday morning.
周二早上我要先带他去看医生

614
00:35:20,790 --> 00:35:23,910
Didn't have time to exercise.Actually felt it in the lecture.
没有时间锻炼 我那天讲课就感觉到了

615
00:35:24,110 --> 00:35:27,470
I was more nervous,more anxious.Makes a big difference.
我觉得更紧张 更焦虑 明显不一样

616
00:35:27,740 --> 00:35:29,150
As we'll talk about,after break,
像我们开学时讲的一样

617
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:33,900
it literally has the same effect as taking an anti-anxiety pill.
锻炼的效果基本和吃抗焦虑药效果一样

618
00:35:34,910 --> 00:35:39,430
So exercise was certainly there,work directly on my emotion.
因此锻炼对我的情绪产生直接的影响

619
00:35:40,970 --> 00:35:44,120
Yoga.Helped me tremendously
瑜伽 在我处理焦虑和…

620
00:35:45,090 --> 00:35:49,930
in dealing with anxiety and lowering that level.
降低焦虑水平上发挥了很大的作用

621
00:35:50,500 --> 00:35:51,730
So this was the emotional.
这是情感上的

622
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:55,680
The other thing,music.Relaxing music.
另一样是音乐 放松的音乐

623
00:35:57,100 --> 00:35:59,900
You know my taste in music.I don't need to repeat it again.
你们知道我喜欢什么音乐 就不重复了

624
00:36:00,370 --> 00:36:06,330
So actually when Tammy and I got married,we moved in together.
我和Tammy结婚后 就搬到了一起住

625
00:36:06,630 --> 00:36:10,990
She couldn't believe my collection of CDs.
她简直不相信我收藏什么样的CD

626
00:36:11,870 --> 00:36:14,060
She said "you don't look that anxious".
她说"你看起来不像这么容易焦虑的人"

627
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,710
Because I had,um,
因为我买的CD是…

628
00:36:15,990 --> 00:36:18,970
"The Most Relaxing Classical Music in the World",
"世界上最放松的经典音乐"

629
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:22,340
"Music for Relaxation","Music for Dealing with Anxiety",
"放松音乐" "降低焦虑的音乐"

630
00:36:22,610 --> 00:36:26,390
silent quiet music- I mean,a whole shelf of the relax...
全是些安静的音乐 整个架子都是

631
00:36:26,590 --> 00:36:28,430
But they relax me! They really help me.
但它们的确对我有帮助 让我得到放松

632
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:35,750
And finally,behavior.Introducing behavior.
最后是行为 我介绍一下行为

633
00:36:36,010 --> 00:36:39,080
So it is through exposure.Initially giving a talk.
通过曝光来治疗恐惧 先是做演讲

634
00:36:39,330 --> 00:36:40,320
Because I want to be a teacher.
因为我想当老师

635
00:36:40,510 --> 00:36:43,850
Giving a talk to my squash team.Giving a talk to my family.
我先给壁球队演讲 给我的家人演讲

636
00:36:44,090 --> 00:36:46,790
Places that were safe for me.
反正是在那些我感觉安心的地方

637
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:50,440
Giving a talk to anyone who would listen.
给任何愿意听的人演讲

638
00:36:50,650 --> 00:36:53,830
Initially small groups and gradually building it up.
从开始的少数人慢慢增加听众数量

639
00:36:54,240 --> 00:36:56,280
Exposure through the imagination.
通过想象来曝光

640
00:36:56,590 --> 00:36:57,640
Once again,
再强调一次

641
00:36:57,870 --> 00:37:02,010
the imaginary thing and over time becoming more  confident.
那种想象久而久之会让人变得更自信

642
00:37:02,340 --> 00:37:03,920
Another thing that for me was very significant
另一样对我极具意义的事是

643
00:37:04,150 --> 00:37:06,670
as an undergrad here- speaking up in section.
作为大学生 在课堂上公开发言

644
00:37:07,980 --> 00:37:09,870
I was terrified of speaking up.
我不敢公开发言

645
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:13,380
And when I decided to do that,I had no doubt in my mind
当我决定那样做 我肯定

646
00:37:13,620 --> 00:37:16,540
that everyone in section could hear my heart beat.
所有人都能听到我的心跳声

647
00:37:16,810 --> 00:37:18,220
Because it was in my head.
因为它就在我脑海中

648
00:37:20,450 --> 00:37:21,700
And yet,gradually,
然而 逐渐地

649
00:37:21,940 --> 00:37:23,710
I spoke up a little bit more and a little bit more,
我慢慢地越来越敢于发言

650
00:37:23,940 --> 00:37:26,030
and then through self-perception theory,
通过自我知觉理论

651
00:37:26,270 --> 00:37:28,950
it actually got better and better and better.
情况变得越来越好

652
00:37:31,740 --> 00:37:33,480
And I still do all these things.
这些事情我一直在坚持做

653
00:37:33,710 --> 00:37:36,310
I still do yoga.I still do exercise regularly.
我还在做瑜伽 定期做运动

654
00:37:36,610 --> 00:37:42,410
I still engage in the CBT approach,the 3 M's.
我还有参加认知行为治疗

655
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:46,880
I keep a journal,which combines very often all three.
我一直有写日记 内容主要和上述三件事有关

656
00:37:47,680 --> 00:37:53,250
And I listen to relaxing music.And it works.It works.
我还会听放松音乐 很有用

657
00:37:53,510 --> 00:37:59,360
Now change is not easy.It is hard.It takes time.However,
改变并不容易 非常困难 需要很多时间 然而

658
00:37:59,650 --> 00:38:02,470
that doesn't mean that the process itself cannot be enjoyable.
但那并不代表 这过程本身没有乐趣

659
00:38:02,730 --> 00:38:06,190
It's not OK when I've changed then I'll be happy.
并不是说改变了就会快乐

660
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:10,220
The process itself is extremely,potentially,extremely rewarding
这过程本身就非常值得

661
00:38:10,450 --> 00:38:13,950
Sometimes difficult.Potentially,very rewarding.
有时很困难 但非常值得

662
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:17,090
The journey as well as the destination.
那旅程本身就跟目的地一样重要

663
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,830
The other important thing to remember about change-
关于改变的另一要点是

